 sampling probabilities of juveniles vs adults are altered relative to the
 default scheme (which uses the age composition of pre-2020 samples).
 The quantitative effects on precision are remarkably small, perhaps because
 so many samples are already available, and because non-lethal sampling
 allows animals to be "future parents".
 At a coarse level, Table
