\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our model does not include calves (ie age 0 animals that are clearly visible
 as such, and always accompanied by their mother), and it does not contain
 a term for calf survival (which is likely different to post-calf juvenile
 survival).
 This might be something to revisit in future.
 Our reasons for omitting calves at this point are largely pragmatic, and
 not necessarily compelling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One reason is to avoid "over-tightening" the population dynamics specification.
 The model already includes terms for per capita rate of calf production,
 juvenile survival, adult survival, 
\emph on
and
\emph default
