\begin_layout Standard
When using Calf\SpecialChar breakableslash
No-calf status for adult females in MOP probs, we need the
 probability that the future (or past) breeding state will be 2, given state
 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 at sampling in year 0.
 Future is simpler:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{gather}
\mathbb{P}\left[B_{+t}=2|B_{0}=b,\text{survives from \ensuremath{0} to \ensuremath{t}},t>0\right]\nonumber \\
=\sum_{b^{*}}\mathbb{P}\left[B_{+t-1}=b^{*}|B_{0}=b,\cdots\right]\times\mathbb{P}\left[B_{+1}=2|B_{0}=b\right]\label{eq:fwd-cond-breed}
\end{gather}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This sets up a recursion, starting from 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}\left[B_{0}=2|B_{0}=b\right]=\mathbf{I}\left(b=2\right)$
\end_inset

 at time 0.
 The second term is direct from the breeding matrix.
 Failure-to-survive (which is assumed independent of breeding status) is
 handled elsewhere in the "forward POP probability" ***.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the case of "past", we also need to condition on age-at-sampling 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

, since we know the female was in state 3 at age 5.
 In this case, "retrospective survival" is automatic (you can't reach age
 7 unless you survived being 6...).
 However, if the female would have been below age 7 at year 
\begin_inset Formula $-t$
\end_inset

, then she could not have been in state 2 then, so the overall probability
 would be 0.
 Bayes' theorem is required; for brevity, we drop the obvious explicit condition
s after the first line.
 Curly braces around a conditioning term indicate that the term in question
 is irrelevant given the other conditionals (e.g., because of a Markov property
 in time).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{gather}
\mathbb{P}\left[B_{-t}=2|B_{0}=b,B_{5-a}=3,t>0,(-t)\geqslant7-a\right]\nonumber \\
=\frac{\mathbb{P}\left[B_{0}=b|B_{-t}=2,\left\{ B_{5-a}=3\right\} \right]\times\mathbb{P}\left[B_{-t}=2|B_{5-a}=3\right]}{\mathbb{P}\left[B_{0}=b|B_{5-a}=3\right]}\nonumber \\
=\frac{\mathbb{P}\left[B_{t}=b|B_{0}=2\right]\times\mathbb{P}\left[B_{-t-(5-a)}=2|B_{0}=3\right]}{\mathbb{P}\left[B_{-\left(5-a\right)}=b|B_{0}=3\right]}\label{eq:bwd-cond-breed}
\end{gather}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All the probabilities in the final equation can be pre-calculated by forward
 recursion, starting from states 2 and 3 respectively.
\end_layout

